post_text:
GSL hosted the State Solo/Ensemble music contest at the St. Pius school. It was a great venue for the contest. Vocally, GSL had 41 entries with 28 receiving “Superior” ratings and 13 receiving “Excellent” ratings. This is outstanding for a vocal contest. Students receiving “PERFORMANCE OF DISTINCTION” award were: Kendra Klobe, Leah Bettcher, Tatyana Tkachenko, Haley, Kirchoff, Jacob Reichow, and Elise Petersen all for solos they performed. Elise Petersen also received a perfect score of 40 on her vocal solo. Twenty-seven students performed solos.

GSL vocal performers received 52 Superior medals and 3 accompanist medals. This was a fantastic showing!!! The judges mentioned several times about the attention to detail and how well prepared the students’ were for their performances. St. Pius was great to work with for hosting the contest at their site. We really appreciate their help and how easy they were to work with to make our contest run smoothly.

post_text:
Congratulations to the GSL Speech Team on their FANTASTIC showing at the Section 4A Speech Tournament held at Mounds Park Academy on Saturday. Only the top three in each category advance to state.

STATE BOUND
Lilly Nikkel: 3rd in Informative Speaking
Leah Bettcher: 3rd in Extemp. Reading

The following students advanced to the final rounds in their respective categories:
Kaitlyn Doolittle: 4th in Great Speeches
Kendra Klobe: 4th in Creative Expression
Anthony LaPlante: 5th in Extemp. Reading
Aubrey Giesen: 7th in Discussion

**Taryn Reichow placed 7th in prelims, just missing a spot in finals.

Way to go team!!

JOB OPENINGS:
Paraprofessional in Special Education
Category: Support Staff/Paraprofessional
Date Posted: 12/08/2017
Location: GSL High School
Date of Availability: 2017-2018 School Year
Date Closing: Open until filled
This paraprofessional position in the special education program at Glencoe-Silver Lake High School (grades 9-12) is for 6.75 hours per day for 172 days during the school year and is a B-21-rated position.
Occasional lifting of 20 to 40 pounds or more may be required. A high school diploma is required. The school district requires applicants for school district positions who receive an offer of employment to submit to a criminal history background check.
For more information about the position contact: Paul Sparby, 7-12 Principal, at 320-864-2401, or at PSparby@gsl.k12.mn.us.
Note: This position is open pending School Board approval.

post_text: Early Childhood Announcement: Every December, the Glencoe-Silver Lake District Office reports to the state the number of children 0-5 years old in our school district. This census determines our ECFE and School Readiness preschool funding, so it is VERY important to us. If you do not receive GSL Early Childhood Family Education mailings, if you have adopted a baby or your baby was born somewhere other than GRHS, if you have moved locally and not left a forwarding address, or if you are new to the area, please contact Becky Dahl in the District Office (320.864.2494 or BDahl@gsl.k12.mn.us) so we can verify if you are on our census.

post_text:
GSL COMMUNITY PEPFEST: On Wednesday, October 18th we will have a community pepfest from 5:30PM - 6:45PM before our football game with Litchfield. The pepfest will be held in the Lincoln parking lot on the west side of Lincoln Elementary. We will have a bunch of teams, organizations, and clubs from our schools participating in the event. We will have our pep band playing, the panther association will be selling food, and the National Guard will have their climbing wall set up. Please keep in mind, there is a 40lb weight limit requirement for kids to participate on the climbing wall. We will also have some games/activities set up and all proceeds will go towards the "Randy Shaver Tackle Cancer" fundraiser.
Please come out and check out the different booths/displays and games as well as socializing with fellow GSL'ers! We hope everyone will stop by and enjoy the event and then stay to cheer on the Panther's football team vs Litchfield!

post_text:
We will be having a family assembly on Monday, September 25th @ 7PM in the high school auditorium. Student Reach Minnesota, the same group that brought us Reggie Dabbs last year, is bringing Eric Samuel Timm to Glencoe on September 25th. Our K-12 kids will get to see him during the school day. Please join us for a family assembly at 7PM!

Eric Samuel Timm is an orator, author, artist, and visionary who uses art to help his audience see what they can not hear. Eric has spoken to over 2 million people in more than 35 countries in a wide range of ven-ues from public schools to music festivals and arenas, and . Eric uses his words and art to captivate and catapult his audiences to action.

Eric will talk about: Patience, Laughter, Being Active, and “Yes” with Parameters. As well as painting.

post_text:
Congratulations to Glencoe Silver Lake students Nick Schmidt and Teagan Hansch. They are the winners at the local level for the 2016-2017 Voice of Democracy and Patriot's Pen competition sponsored by Glencoe VFW Post 5102 and Glencoe VFW Post 5102 Ladies Auxiliary. Nick and Teagan were presented with checks for their participation.

Voice of Democracy is an audio essay contest for high school students in grades 9-12. The annual contest, which is designed to foster patriotism, allows students the opportunity to voice their opinion in a three to five minute essay based on an annual theme. The 2016-2017 theme was “My Responsibility to America.”

Patriot’s Pen is a nationwide competition that gives students in grades 6, 7, and 8 the opportunity to write an essay expressing their views on democracy. “The America I Believe In” was the theme for 2016-2017.

post_text:
Wow! What a weekend for the Knowledge Bowlers! On Friday, at our Subregional meet, all five GSL teams placed in the top ten. Four will go on to the Regional meet on March 9. Supernova won the meet by a whopping 55 points, while Antimatter placed second, and other GSL teams finished in 5th, 6th, and 10th.

Then at Sartell on Saturday, Supernova won a 55-team varsity meet with 124 points, beating both Chaska and St. John's Prep. Antimatter finished in 11th place (in the top 20%!)
Congratulations!

post_text:
GSL Knowledge Bowl went to New London-Spicer on Saturday.
We took eight teams - 1 varsity, 2 JV, and 5 junior high. All teams finished in the top half of their divisions.

Our varsity won the 13-team Varsity division with a score of 120. The second-place team, Ortonville, had 88.5.

Our JV took second only to YME. The second team finished sixth out of the twelve teams.

One of our junior high teams won their 28-team division, with a margin of 23 over the second-place team, again excellent! Our
other four teams finished 8th, 11th, 13th and 14th.

Altogether, it was a great day for GSL KB!!
